(ns eve.deftype-proto.wasm
  "WASM Slab Allocator Memory Module.

   Unlike eve.wasm-mem which uses a single shared WebAssembly.Memory,
   this module manages MULTIPLE WebAssembly.Memory instances — one per slab.
   Each slab gets its own WASM module instance backed by its own SAB.

   ARCHITECTURE:
   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │   Slab 0 (32B)  │ Slab 1 (64B) │ ... │ Slab 5 (1024B)   │
   │   WASM Instance  │ WASM Instance│     │ WASM Instance     │
   │   SAB + Bitmap   │ SAB + Bitmap │     │ SAB + Bitmap      │
   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │           slab_bitmap.wat (shared WASM module)             │
   │   bitmap_find_free_simd  │  bitmap_alloc_cas               │
   │   bitmap_free            │  bitmap_count_free_simd         │
   │   memcpy                 │  bytes_equal                    │
   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

   Each slab creates a WebAssembly.Memory with shared:true.
   The same WASM module (slab_bitmap.wasm) is instantiated once per slab,
   with the slab's memory as the import."
  (:require [eve.mem :as mem]))

